In universe there’s no such thing as canon, so these could possibly just not be in the same universe. However, I’ve always disliked the “no canon” excuse for things, so I’ll attempt to justify why I personally think it’s the Foundation’s biggest failure:

the Foundation couldn’t destroy a rogue nation that could threaten the geopolitical situation in the Pacific. Omega-7 did something horrible, ending in the death of many personnel. However, in terms of sheer overall threat to the geopolitical status quo, 4036 was a much, much bigger threat to the foundation. Failing to fully contain it wouldn’t have actually removed the threat itself, just limiting its scope and power at the moment.
Allowing to be strong armed by a smaller, tinier organization would have been a sign of weakness. It was not only a containment failure but a personal failure — if the foundation couldn’t contain a tiny island, what chance did they have of something much, much bigger?


These are just my reasons.

